            <h3 id="policy-header">SNAP Policy:</h3>

            <ol>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports must fall under a limit of a one mile radius.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports will be provided from off-campus housing, to campus and from campus, to off-campus housing.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports will be provided when on campus to anywhere else on campus.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> A and D term a SNAP transport can be to or from Price Chopper all days of the week besides
                    Friday and Saturday from 6pm onward. For B and C term a SNAP transport can be to or from
                    Price Chopper all days of the week besides Friday and Saturday from 4pm onward.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports are not used for rides to shopping centers, restaurants, bars, or any other commercial
                    locations.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports may be provided to WPI students traveling to and from Union Station for traveling
                    purposes only, we advise that you give a 45 minute warning so that dispatch can fit this in their
                    schedule. </li>
                <li class="policy-list"> Transports are not allowed by law to transport any forms of drugs or alcohol. SNAP drivers are
                    authorized to view any enclosed packages and /or containers.</li>
                <li class="policy-list"> You must have a VALID WPI ID and be an active member of the WPI community to utilize
                    SNAP services.</li>
            </ol>

